@startuml
title Public Resume Flow — Executive View (AI Owns Real-Time)
autonumber

actor "Candidate UI" as FE
participant "Monolith API" as MON
participant "AI Service\n(Parse + Orchestrate)" as AI
participant "OpenAI + pgvector" as EMB

== Upload (~0.3s) ==
FE -> MON: Upload resume
MON --> FE: 201 Created

note right of MON
Atomic write:
Resume + Outbox event
end note

== Phase 1 — Contact Parse (~1s) ==
MON -> AI: resume.uploaded (event)
AI -> AI: Extract contact info (1 LLM call)
AI -> FE: SignalR "contact" parsed

== Phase 2 — Parallel Sections (~9s) ==
AI -> AI: 5 parallel LLM calls\n(skills, work, education, certs, projects)
AI -> FE: SignalR per section (progressive)

note right of FE
UI updates live as each section completes
end note

== Phase 3 — Embeddings (~0.5s) ==
AI -> EMB: 3 parallel embeddings\n(full + skills + experience)
EMB --> AI: vectors stored in pgvector

== Phase 4 — Match Explanations (~6s) ==
AI -> EMB: Top 10 jobs (pgvector similarity)\n+ 4 parallel LLM explanation batches
EMB --> AI: Explanations + scores cached

AI -> FE: SignalR (matching complete)

note over FE
Total: ~19s end-to-end
No blocking. No polling. Event-driven.
Subsequent requests served from cache.
end note

@enduml